Sichuan Chuantou Jumps Most in 8 Months as Share Sale Approved

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-28T03:13:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/sichuan-chuantou-jumps-most-in-8-months-as-share-sale-approved.html
Sichuan Chuantou Energy Co. jumped
the most in more than eight months in Shanghai trading after
shareholders approved its plan to raise no more than 2.2 billion
yuan through a share sale.  Sichuan Chuantou rose 5.3 percent to 14.76 yuan as of
10:34 a.m. local time, heading for its biggest gain since Oct.
11, 2010. The company plans to sell no more than 163
million A-shares, according to a statement to the  Shanghai
Stock Exchange . The proceeds will be used to increase its
stake in an affiliated hydropower company, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  